ch, patients will no longer need to risk going to the hospitals to check the progression of their disease. My work at Abbvie solidified my passion for helping people with [role]ing and taught me valuable lessons about the business side aspects of research and development.\n\nAt GHX, I am a Research Analyst, providing subject matter expertise to evaluate various FDA-approved medical devices. This experience has given me a deep understanding of the medical device industry and the regulations that govern it. I help provide doctors, nurses, and health system executives with life-saving data to make the best purchasing decisions. Using medical product spending data provided by partners, I can provide evidence-based savings strategies and spend utilization insights. In my role, I am also tasked with improving Business to Business (B2B) relationships with hospitals. This requires me to listen and understand their exact problem and how best to address it. I have developed strong communication and networking skills as I am constantly communicating with device manufacturers to gain critical insider knowledge about their products that may not otherwise be available. This experience will be incredibly valuable for the position of [role] at [company]. The medical device industry is heavily regulated, and my understanding of the regulations will benefit [company] as they work to bring its biofeedback technology to the masses. Additionally, my experience in B2B relationships and my ability to understand and address the needs of hospitals will be helpful as [company] works to bring its technology to hospitals and other healthcare providers. My ability to collect product-specific data from the FDA, peer-reviewed journals, and device manufacturers to allow clients to understand product functionality fully will also be valuable for [company].\n\nI am excited about the opportunity to join [company] and use my machine learning and artificial intelligence skills to drive real-time model 